The paper deals with a robotic grasping task using visual information, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The approach involves using a convolutional neural network (CNN) for feature extraction, which suggests the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses learning mappings between visual features and grasp points, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and learning theory (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach using a grasping dataset, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
